Executive Summary
On 29 January 2026, Desktop II experienced a critical audio subsystem failure affecting the system’s audio enhancement and monitoring applications.
The issue was caused by incompatible generic audio drivers introduced through sequential third-party driver update utilities, which overwrote platform-specific driver components required by the audio enhancement stack.
The system presented the following error:
	“The current system is not supported, or the audio driver has not been properly installed.”
A structured remediation procedure was performed, including driver store cleanup, hidden component removal, and clean installation of verified platform-specific drivers. Full functionality was restored. The system audio stack is now stable, clean, and fully operational.

