Issue Summary
After multiple sequential driver updates, the audio enhancement application failed to initialize and displayed the following error:
	“The current system is not supported, or the audio driver has not been properly installed.”
Observed symptoms:
• Audio enhancement application crashing on launch
• Audio monitoring tool non-functional
• Missing advanced audio controls
• Loss of platform-specific audio enhancement features

Background
The audio stack is tightly integrated with platform-specific drivers and requires platform-dependent driver components.
Critical dependencies included:
• Audio driver package with platform-specific extensions
• Audio processing service components
• Audio framework services
• Enhancement application stack
Generic drivers lack these custom integrations and can break compatibility. Sequential installation of third-party driver updater packages introduced incompatible generic drivers, corrupting the platform-specific driver chain and contaminating the driver store.

