Resolution and Preventive Recommendations
Critical Preventive Control:
Avoid using third-party driver updater tools for platform-specific drivers.
Approved Driver Sources:
Use only verified platform-specific driver packages. Avoid generic driver installers.
Driver Maintenance Best Practices:
• Perform periodic driver validation (pnputil /enum-drivers)
• Maintain applications via official updates only
• Avoid mixing generic and platform-specific drivers
• Maintain clean and controlled driver environment

Conclusion
The audio driver conflict was successfully resolved through complete driver stack cleanup and structured reinstall of verified platform-specific drivers.
Desktop II audio subsystem is fully stable, functional, and operating under a correct, vendor-supported configuration.
